<style>
	.ls-app-wraps{
		display:flex;
	}
	.ls-app-wraps h4{
		margin-left:10px; margin-top:10px;
	}
	.ls-app-wraps img{
		height:37px;
	}
	.ls-app-descs{
		margin-left:5px;
	}
	.ls-app-button{
		text-align:left; width:100%;
	}
	.ls-app-button span{
		font-weight:bold; color:#5E94B6;
	} 
	.ls-hide-button{
		display:none;
	}
</style>

<h2>Mississippi</h2>
<div>
    The Mississippi Freshwater Assessment is a multi-tool platform that provides a wealth of information on the quality and quantity of water flowing down Louisiana’s bayous, rivers and streams and the potential effects of future changes in climate and water use on that water flow. For additional project information, visit the <a href="https://freshwaternetwork.org/" target="_blank"><b>freshwatenetwork.org</b></a>.
</div>

<h3>Get Started</h3>

<div class="button ls-app-button">	
	<div class="ls-app-wraps">
		<img src="img/regional-planning.png">
		<h4 class="color-primary">Map Layers</h4>
	</div>
	<div class="ls-app-descs">
		View and interact with freshwater data layers including: rivers, USGS and NOAA stream gages, watersheds, wetlands, political boundaries, managed areas and land cover..
	</div>
</div>	
<button class="button launch-plugin ls-hide-button" data-plugin-name="regional-planning"></button>

<div class="button ls-app-button">	
	<div class="ls-app-wraps">
		<img src="img/hydroFlow.png">
		<h4 class="color-primary">Hydro Flows</h4>
	</div>
	<div class="ls-app-descs">
		A statewide hydrologic model for Mississippi’s watersheds. 
	</div>
</div>	
<button class="button launch-plugin ls-hide-button" data-plugin-name="HydroFlow"></button>

<div class="button ls-app-button">	
	<div class="ls-app-wraps">
		<img src="img/feature-compare.png">
		<h4 class="color-primary">Feature Compare</h4>
	</div>
	<div class="ls-app-descs">
		Compare attributes of up to 3 features.
	</div>
</div>	
<button class="button launch-plugin ls-hide-button" data-plugin-name="feature_compare"></button>

<div class="button ls-app-button">	
	<div class="ls-app-wraps">
		<img src="img/hydrologic-alterations.png">
		<h4 class="color-primary">Hydrologic Alterations</h4>
	</div>
	<div class="ls-app-descs">
		Description of the Hydrologic Alterations app.
	</div>
</div>	
<button class="button launch-plugin ls-hide-button" data-plugin-name="hydrologic-alterations"></button>

<script>
	$(".ls-app-button").click(function(c){
		$(c.currentTarget).next().trigger("click")
	})
</script>
